deck_excerpt: An inexpensive Blue-Eyes White Dragon deck built by a returning player after 15-20 years.
deck_description: This deck represents the earliest incarnation of a Blue-Eyes White Dragon deck built using the Saga of the Blue-Eyes White Dragon structure deck as a skeleton and modifying it with additional inexpensive support cards. It will only perform competitively in the most casual of settings. UPDATE 10/25/21: Embarrassing as they may be, these two early Blue-Eyes White Dragon decks were my re-entry point to playing YuGiOh after nearly 18 years since I last played. In the time since I built this initial deck from a single copy of the Saga of the BEWD structure deck, I've learned the basic theory and game mechanics of YuGiOh and run an incomparably better deck. This is a good reminder that less than six months ago, I didn't know a damn thing about this game.

deck_excerpt: A Drytron with many winning conditions, including a Tzolkin - Scarlight Red Dragon Archfiend combo, this deck also hinder bad first hand by adding Lev
deck_description:
Edit: Fixed to match TCG format
Trying a semi-competitive Drytron deck with many winning conditions, including a Tzolkin, including (but not limited to):
  1. Drytron Meteonis Draconids (beatdown), note that it can attack every SS monster, once each.
  2. Tzolkin + Scarlight Red Dragon Archfiend (burn damage MP2), most monster are under 3000 ATK, except Draconids. Therefore, an additional 2000 burn damage is nice.
  3. Clear Wing Synchro Dragon (Herald + 1 Drytron), for bad starting hand.
Going 2nd:
  1. DRNM (for Winda/ VFD/ any other control), negate them all then use Draconids wipe
  2. Black Rose Dragon (Herald + 1 Drytron) as a cheap Raigeki + Feather Duster for bad starting hand
For consistency:
  1. 2 Mu-Beta Fafnir: clear you field, +1 material. 1st turn: send missing Drytron to GY. 2nd turn: send Draconids to GY.
  2. 2 Fafnir: a good field spell, so you want to have it as frequent as possible
  3. Foolish burial: send missing Drytron to GY.
Some plays I recorded: https://youtu.be/yQ7XpyXAgc4

deck_excerpt: The dock that makes too many big numbers.
deck_description: Welcome! I’m actually super happy about this new support because I did ask for it before, now that it’s here I’m extremely happy to present to you, deciphering the ciphers (pun COMPLETELY intended)! So I had an overview of the new cards, the new biplane is worth playing triplane of. Double exposure became a 3 of because it wasn’t searchable and did have some neat effects. The cipher interference was actually put at one, the only thing it does is push for game and it’s searchable. For the ciphers that already exist all main deck monsters are at 3 except entangler who’s at one. I put 3 rank up and the traps are mostly useless but one double cipher can be played, if you don’t want to play double cipher you can definitely replace it with upstart goblin. For the extra deck I have 2 X dragon because it self overlays, one Neo cipher because it’s a solid boss to do a very hard push for game, 2 cipher blade dragon for the free rank up, and 3 of the original cipher dragon because that’s what powers up and makes plays for the deck.  For the techs you’ll probably understand most of them but I’ll explain anyways:  Storm cipher has the namesake of the cipher and is searchable via cynet mining, its only there for those reasons  Number 97, 38, and 100 are the dragobulon engine, it’s an otk engine that’s really good because of the sheer amounts of ranks you make in this build.  I also added a utopia engine (with photon) using utopia double, double or nothing, the new version of number 99, photon thrasher, and number 90. Using double to summon number 99 and then summon number 90 with number 99’s effect. Next turn 90 attaches a thrasher from your deck to itself for another negate. This also provides 20 rankings on the field for numeron dragon.  And of course Zeus because that’s the xyz monster to end all xyz monsters.     I hope you like it! Thanks for reading and I’ll se you next time!

By putting a lot of its focus on the fans, "Hail to the Deadites" explains why the film series has actually become as beloved as it is. Check out the trailer for the documentary below: https://aquietplaceukraine.wildapricot.org/ "Hail to the Deadites" premiered (and was praised) at the Canadian Fantasia Film Festival in August last year, and is now getting a digital release on July 27. deck_excerpt: Earth Machine is the 2nd best deck after pendulum. It’s a combo control deck that focuses on out grinding your opponent. Earth Machine is super fun an
deck_description:
1.  Earth Machine is the 2nd best deck after pendulum. It’s a combo control deck that focuses on out grinding your opponent. It also doesn’t typically use negates as interruption, instead relying on traps and destruction. The main goal in any duel going 1st is to get your engine flowing, survive your opponent’s turn, and then proceed to pop off now you have all your best cards in your GY and hand. The best build of the deck is no longer budget due to Machina Metalcruncher rising to 14$, but I will leave a budget list below. 
Strengths: Infinitracks let you modulate your levels to access a large variety of ranks you usually wouldn’t be able to, meaning you can hard summon Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS – Sky Thunder!   The Engine is not too large, allowing to you to main deck about 6-12 going 2nd cards.   Forbidden Droplet is incredible here because it can function both as a trap and a board breaker. Since your turn one board isn’t extraordinarily strong, you can use droplet as additional interruption. The basic 1 card combo alone creates 2 monsters on field that don’t do much that you can send, and since you only need 1 card to combo, you can afford to send a lot of your hand as well.  You are not completely reliant on your extra deck. Even if you are locked out of it, you still have Machina Fortress and Machina Citadel.  The deck plays well under skill drain due to high attack monsters and easy summoning conditions.  This deck also has a searchable El Shaddoll Winda out in the form of Machina Fortress.  Weaknesses: This deck is extremely GY reliant, so any cards like Dimension Shifter and Macro Cosmos are very detrimental.  Combos lose hard to most hand traps. Droll and Lock Bird, Ash Blossom and Joyous Spring, Nibiru, the Primal Being, and Gamma are some of the worst.  If your normal summon is removed from the field, you will not be able to use any Infinitracks in your hand.  You do not play many extenders so playing through multiple interruptions can be tough.        1 card main combo  This combo needs either Machina Metalcruncher, Infinitrack Harvester, Machina Redeployment, or Heavy Forward  All these cards are played at three, so you have 12 cards combo starters.      1.) I will use Machina Metalcruncher as my starter. Normal summon Machina Metalcruncher, revealing 3 Infinitrack Brutal Dozer and searching one of them.    2.) Activate Infinitrack Brutal Dozer in hand tributing Machina Metalcruncher. In special summon of Infinitrack Brutal Dozer the secondary effect will activate allowing you to summon Infinitrack Trencher from deck. Using Dozer and Trencher, XYZ summon Infinitrack River Stormer.     3.) Activate Infinitrack River Stormer effect detaching Infinitrack Trencher to search Super Express Bullet Train.   (If you already have it then you can search Heavy Freight Train Derricrane. At the end of the combo revive bullet with the Double Headed Anger Knuckle, and the summon Derricrane from your hand to make Number 81: Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Super Dora.)    4.) Special summon Super Express Bullet Train Linking into Infinitrack Goliath using Infinitrack River Stormer also link again using Infinitrack Goliath and Super Express Bullet Train into Ancient Gear Ballista.      5.) Ballista will add Ancient Gear Box triggering its effect to add Infinitrack Tunneller to hand. Use Infinitrack Tunneller effect to tribute Ancient Gear Ballista, summoning itself then link it into Infinitrack Goliath    6.) Using Infinitrack Trencher effect in GY to summon back Dozer who we link off to summon other Infinitrack Goliath. Finally, we will summon Double Headed Anger Knuckle.     7.) If there is another level 10 special summon in your hand go on and use it on the summon of Knuckle, then use the effect of Knuckle discarding ancient gear box to summon back express going into number 81 activating its effect detaching Express.    8.) Infinitrack Tunneller will shuffle back 5 Earth machine monsters unto the deck your targets will be your starter, all 3 Infinitrack Goliath, and Ancient Gear Ballista    Now on your opponent’s turn use Double Headed Anger Knuckle effect to discard the Ancient Gear Box in your hand to special summon back the Super Express Bullet Train. This means that at the end of the turn, if your Bullet was destroyed you can add back box and search Infinitrack Anchor Drill. This leaves you with a straightforward way to make a rank 8 and a Dozer in hand. In your GY you’ll have a River Stormer, Anger Knuckle, Bullet Train, and Box, which should all help make some strong follow up plays.    This is the main combo of Earth Machine. This was created by the pioneer of the deck, Aerosol_tcg, and I will link more of his fantastic combos below.         If you draw the box….  The starter in this combo matters. Harvester is going to be better here, but Cruncher can be used if there is a Trencher in GY.  Now drawing Ancient Gear Box sucks, as it’s the only garnet in this deck, but you can get out of it and get the engine flowing anyway.  1.) Normal summon Infinitrack Harvester and add to hand a copy of Infinitrack Brutal Dozer. Using Infinitrack Harvestor. link summon Infinitrack Goliath.     2.) Activate Infinitrack Brutal Dozer effect in hand to tribute the Infinitrack Goliath and special summon itself. Infinitrack Brutal Dozer will summon Infinitrack Tunneller.     3.) Using Infinitrack Brutal Dozer and Infinitrack Tunneller overlay into Infinitrack River Stormer. Activate Infinitrack River Stormer effect by detaching Infinitrack Trencher to search Super Express Bullet Train and summon it.     4.) Link summon another Infinitrack Goliath using Infinitrack River Stormer, then link summon Double Headed Anger Knuckle using Infinitrack Goliath and Super Express Bullet Train.    5.) Use Double Headed Anger Knuckle effect to discard the Ancient Gear Box to summon back the Super Express Bullet Train.     6.) Activate Infinitrack River Stormer effect in GY to tribute the Double Headed Anger Knuckle.    7.) Use Infintrack Tunneller effect in GY to shuffle back 2 Infinitrack Goliath, Double Headed Anger Knuckle, Ancient Gear Box, and the Infinitrack Brutal Dozer/Starter.     8.) Link summon Ancient Gear Ballista to search the Ancient Gear Box triggering Box effect to add Infinitrack Trencher.     9.) Tribute Ancient Gear Ballista to summon Infinitrack Trencher, then use it to link summon Infinitrack Goliath. Use Infinitrack Trencher effect in GY to summon back Infinitrack Harvester. Use Harvester then  to link summon Double Headed Anger Knuckle.     This combo ends the same as a 1st but takes an extra card. Thanks to Yishan for showing this, drawing Box can be very irritating.    Budget List combos   Budget List                                                                  Main Deck:  1x Machina Citadel                                                                       1x Super Express Bullet Train                                 1x Machina Irradiator                                                 1x Machina Fortress  1x Infinitrack Tunneller  3x Infinitrack Brutal Dozer                                                                        2x Infinitrack Trencher  1x Machina Unclaspare  1x Infinitrack Anchor Drill  3x Machina Gearframe  1x Machina Possesstorage  1x Ancient Gear Box  3x Infinitrack Harvester  3x Effect Veiler  3x Machina Redeployment  3x Heavy Forward  2x E.M.R.  3x Torrential Tribute  3x Machina Overdrive   ---------  Extra Deck:  1x Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Juggernaut Liebe  1x Number 81: Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Super Dora  1x Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Gustav Max  1x Infinitrack Earth Slicer  1x Phantom Fortress Enterblathnir  1x Infinitrack Mountain Smasher  1x Infinitrack River Stormer  2x Gear Gigant X  1x Platinum Gadget  1x Double Headed Anger Knuckle  1x Ancient Gear Ballista  3x Infinitrack Goliath  ---------  Other Combos   Basic Combos                              Machina Redeployment Combos   Anti-Light Combos   Side/Main Deck Card Options 

3x Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring  

3x Paleozoic Dinomischus 

3x Trap Trick 

3x Nibiru, the Primal Being 

3x E.M.R

deck_excerpt: Fun deck using level 4 winged-beast normal monsters, 1 tribute WIND monsters, and WIND Dragons!
deck_description: This is a fun deck using level 4 WIND winged-beast normal monsters, 1 tribute WIND monsters, and WIND Dragons.  Simorgh, Bird of Ancestry, counts as a normal monster in hand, so it works with Wind Effigy, Ancient Rules, or Heart of The Underdog, making for a total of 26 targets for that card.  Level 4 normal monsters can be cheated out with Unexpected Dai, (go for Spirit Of The Books first if you're using it as material) Rescue Rabbit, or Cry Havoc!  If they are clogging your hand, fuse them! Or pendulum summon them with the Dragoons of Draconia cards, which also give your normal monsters battle effects! Since rituals and normal monsters have great synergy, I fit in a small ritual engine with Tempest, Dragon Ruler of Storms to search Knight of Armor Dragon, Sonic Bird to search the ritual art cards, and Nowruz Elise/Armed Dragon Lv5 as special summoning targets.  The 1 Tribute WIND monsters were mainly chosen for their high attack values, but each one has some utility as well.  The one non-WIND tribute monster, Knight of the Red Lotus, is also able to cheat itself out like DAD but for normal monsters.  I don't know why I made this crappy deck!

deck_excerpt: They actually aren't bad now!  Worth looking at if only for the funsies!
deck_description: Truly awful with just what they had in Blazing Vortex, Lightning Overdrive brought a lot of much needed support for this archetype.  S/T removal with Mammud and Big Blow and effect negates with Dignity.  Still a very battle focused archetype it can at least stand a bit of a chance against other decks now.  Opening hand should have you opening with Mountain (or Terraforming at the least), and one or two monsters.  The deck certainly has enough searchers in it now to have a consistent opening rip.  Mammud and Orpis can normal themselves with no tribute and Gactos can special himself if you normaled that turn.  Fortia, Wento, and Gactos can search if your opponent sends them by card effect; Fortia to hand, Wendo and Gactos special summon.  Two Extravagance for slightly more consistence and Cross Over to help remove monsters.  Big Blow is essentially an archetype Heavy Storm Duster when your opponent makes a War Rock leave the field: basically everything except for battle destruction as it can only be activated in the Main Phase).  I use Spirit as a Battle Phase Monster Reborn but I am sure other people smarter than me could make better use for it.  Extra deck is all Link Monsters for various toolbox needs you might have but I think putting some XYZ Monsters in wouldn't be a bad idea.  I just am not sure which.  Side deck isn't anything special, Monster Reborn, Expendable Dai, and Mind Crush I'm all a little iffy on.  Alternates I would put in are a third Solemn Judgment and Infinite Impermanence.  The rest of the deck are all staple powerhouses.  Some fine tuning can be done if you feel.  I think it's actually not a completely awful deck now.     EDIT: Removed two Borrelswords for Verte Anaconda and Dragoon.  Moved Pots to side deck; added third Judgment as well.  Added third Dignity to main deck as well as RE Fusion, Dragon, and DM.

deck_excerpt: Insect Stun based around Scary Moth and Metamorphosed Insect Queen ft. Kaiju engine!
deck_description: Insect Stun based around Scary Moth and Metamorphosed Insect Queen.  Kaiju engine synergizes because it heavily uses insects and will allow you to take the problem cards off your opponent's board.  Transmodify, Insect Imitation, and Cocoon of Ultra Evolution all let you cheat your main monsters out of the deck. Primitive Butterfly can be used with these cards to summon Scary Moth.  Scary Moth is basically summon limit on legs, but it is also untargetable and cannot be destroyed with Metamorphosed Insect Queen on board alongside it.  Resonance Insect, Gokipole, Killer Needle, Foolish Burial and Gold Sarc form a mini engine.  Use Picofalena to equip Retaliating C from deck, link away with it and you will be able to grab a Parasite Paranoid from deck.  You can equip Parasite Paranoid or Moon Mirror Shield to you or your opponent's monsters so they can be tributed for Cocoon of Ultra Evolution. Moon Mirror shield can also make one of your boss monsters even more unkillable.
To solely depend on the single Man-Eater Bug I drew in progression.

deck_description: RIP Union Carrier, we've got some clunkier combos that still work without him.  Ash-proof combo: Pieces - 1 Hangar + 1 A/B/C OR 1 Unauthorized + 2 A/B/C Activate Hangar, tutor C if not in hand, otherwise tutor B Summon C, equip with Driver Remove Driver to equip Torque Tune Gear to C Unequip TTG, link C + TTG into Halq CL1 Halq CL2 C, resolve C to summon B or A, tutor Deskbot with Halq Link Halq + Deskbot into Auroradon, recur Deskbot Synchro Borreload Savage Dragon with Deskbot + token + A/B (use A to grab back TTG or B to tutor another union) Activate Auroradon saccing 2 tokens to SS Coltwing, Coltwing returns Deskbot Synchro Shooting Riser Dragon with Deskbot + 2 tokens Send missing A/B/C piece off of Shooting Riser Dragon to make it level 3 Synchro Shooting Riser + Coltwing for FA Dawn Dragster Make ABC  End board - Auroradon, ABC, Borreload, FA Dawn Dragster  Nibiru-proof combo: Pieces - 1 Hangar + 1 A/B/C OR 1 Unauthorized + 2 A/B/C Activate Hangar, tutor A if not in hand, otherwise tutor C Summon C, equip with Driver Remove Driver to equip B to C Unequip B, link B + C into Barricadeborg Blocker CL1 C, CL2 B, CL3 Borg Pitch A to Borg, tutor TTG with B, SS TTG with C Link Borg + TTG into Halq, tutor Deskbot with Halq Link Halq + Deskbot into Auroradon, recuring Deskbot Synchro Herald of the Arc Light with Deskbot + token Activate Auroradon saccing 2 tokens to tutor Coltwing, recuring Deskbot Synchro Deskbot + 2 tokens for FA Dawn Dragster Make ABC  End board - Auroradon, ABC, FA Dawn Dragster, Herald of the Arc Light, Mecha Phantom Beast Coltwing  Simple ABC combo (not Nib or Ash proof): Pieces - 1 Hangar OR 1 Unauthorized Reactivation + 1 A/B/C Activate Hangar, tutor B Summon B, equip with Driver Remove Driver to equip B with C Unequip B, link B + C into Platinum Gadget Tutor A with B SS A with Platinum Gadget Make ABC  End board - Platinum Gadget, ABC  2-card Link Climb: Pieces - 1 Hangar + 1 A/B/C OR 1 Unauthorized Reactivation + 2 A/B/C Activate Hangar If A or C is in hand tutor B, otherwise tutor C Summon C, equip with Driver Remove Driver, equip C with A Unequip A, link C + A into Knightmare Phoenix CL1 C, CL2 A, CL2 Phoenix Resolve Phoenix (don't pitch B), use A to recycle C, SS C with C Link C + Phoenix into Knightmare Unicorn CL1 C, CL2 Unicorn Resolve Unicorn (don't pitch B), SS B with C Link B + Unicorn into Accesscode Talker CL1 B, CL2 Accesscode Tutor anything with B Make ABC  End board - deck_excerpt: Use Fallen of Albaz's effect on your opponent's turn with Ninjutsu Art of Super-Transformation!
deck_description: This deck focuses on using our opponent's monsters for fusion summons.  This is done with Lair of Darkness + Super Poly as well as by using the new Albaz fusion cards that were just released in LIOV.  Using Ninja Grandmaster Hanzo with Ninjutsu Art of Super-Transformation, we can use Fallen of Albaz's effect proactively on the opponent's turn to fuse their monsters with Albaz and interrupt their plays.  Super transformation can also summon Diabolos, Pankratops, or Dark Horus, a tech card which summons a level 4 Dark monster from the graveyard when your opponent resolves a spell card, you can use this effect to special summon Albaz and interrupt their plays with a fusion.  Melody of Awakening Dragon will get Diabolos and/or Dark Horus to your hand, Foolish Burial/Dragon Shrine will get Diabolos or Keeper of the Shrine to the GY. Keeper of the Shrine can be tributed to normal summon out Diabolos or Dark Horus from the hand.  Ahrima and Lilith tribute themselves and bring out Diabolos from the hand or GY.  By using Lilith's effect to choose the 2 viruses (or InfImp) we want and trap trick, we can always get the virus we need while only main decking 2 copies of each, saving deck space. Virus cards give info, rip cards from the opponent's hand, and can tribute our opponent's monsters while we have Lair of Darkness active.  Lair of Darkness also allows the deck to reliably use Super Polymerization to fuse away 2 or 3 of the opponent's monsters into Predaplant Triphyoverutum or Starving Venom Fusion Dragon at spell speed 4.  I would love to hear any suggestions to improve the deck!

(I advise to let the Rokket on the field and use Dillingerous Dragon, Elpy and Red-Eyes Darkness Metal Dragon for the link-4 and use the effect of the Rokket during your opponnent turn with your link-4). If you can have 2 more level 4 monster on the field make Borrelload then do the same action as above but with Pisty, summon Dillingerous Dragon from your banished zone and make a third Link-4 monster.
A neat deck that is still budget even with zeus eating 70% of that budget.
